<h2 id="report">6. Reports & Analytics</h2>
<p>The pharmacy management system generates reports to check the wholesales’ performance. Reporting & analytics prepare
   for the pre-requirement of drugs. It also automatically manages the inventory. The feature calculates the number of 
   needed medications. The reporting system enhances sales and ROI (Return of Investment). Moreover, it provides a full 
   report of the pharma business activities.
    </p>
<p>Furthermore, the reporting feature prepares classified sales reports. They are also arranged category-wise and
   product-wise. The management system creates customized reports for marketing purposes. Thus, critical insights lead 
   to decision-making. The data is also essential for monitoring & audits.

   The system manages patients’ information and drug supply chains. Besides, Revenue reports improve sales and purchases.
   Reporting also helps to remain compliant and check anomalies in the system. The feature determines performance metrics 
   and builds a budgeting roadmap. Hence, it enables to obtain insights and detect suspicious patterns.
</p>

   
<h2 id="center">7. Centralized Database</h2>
<p>Data is a crucial element of the pharma business. Furthermore, a centralized database holds the patient’s data at a
   centralized location. The pharmacy management system provides easy data retrieval. It also manages transactional 
   records. The system eliminates data loss. Additionally, it stores data about drugs and medications. Thus, the setup 
   provides information for drug availability.

   A centralized database also enhances the patient’s convenience for secure data access. The system simplifies the data
   search. The dynamic system minimizes the workforce. Besides, the centralized system enables drug report generation.
    </p>
<p>The system empowers businesses to operate smoothly. Moreover, it provides complete visibility of inventory and sales
   with real-time data analysis. The system boosts decision-making to maintain medical records. The centralized database 
   feature also works well for organizations, even those with small databases. It works as a communication device within 
   pharma staff.
</p>

      
<h2 id="restore">8. Feature of Restore & Backup System of pharmacy management system</h2>
<p>What happens when the data is lost suddenly? The business operations may stop abruptly. Data such as patient records
   and inventory is always at risk. A restore and backup system avoids unnecessary data loss. This system eliminates 
   technical errors while retrieving data quickly.

   The pharmacy management system provides automatic backup schedules. Data-backup is done regularly. Additionally, a
   Data restoration service safely secures the data. It also avoids interruptions in business functioning. The

   pharmacy management system offers a growth opportunity. An ideal system also possesses zero size limitations for data
   backup. Hence, the alert system informs about successful backup completion.
   </p>

   <h2 id="customer">9. Customer Management System</h2>
<p>Customers are at the core of any system designed for businesses. Pharmacy management systems must have an automated
   solution to manage patients. CMS also keeps a record of the patient’s data. Furthermore, it is a dynamic solution that 
   adds new customers. Well-organized CMS holds customer responses and feedback. Hence, Pharmacists develop pharmacy 
   business strategies to manage customer requirements.

   A customer management system is a robust solution for small and medium-sized pharmacies. It possesses an attractive, 
   user-friendly interface. The system also leads to easy navigation. After every update, it automatically refreshes the 
   patient’s list, Moreover, it allows pharmacists to provide information at their fingertips. The system manages multiple 
   patient profiles. Hence, it is reliable for patient therapy management.
    </p>

       
