   patient records. E-prescribing software integration to control medical receipts.

   POS (Point of Sale) integration enables record transactions and inventory management. IVR (Interactive Voice Response) 
   (Interactive Voice Response) integration improves patients’ interaction with pharmacy staff. The pharmacy management 
   system combines with DHL for order management.
    </p>
<p>The system also sends delivery messages or alerts. The third-party software improves visibility and clarity.
   They manage account receivables and insurance claims. The solutions optimize pharma stores for effective services. 
   Allow easy deployment in an IT environment. Need minimal time for claims management.
</p>

<h2 id="regulatory">11. Regulatory & Compliance of pharmacy management system</h2>
<p>The compliance regulations cover each dimension of pharma practice. POS solutions address compliance for drug ordering
   and e-prescription.
    </p>
<p>US and EU regulators use advanced technologies to standardize the dispense of medication. The federal law Drug Supply
   Chain Security Act (DSCSA) protects against the dispensing of fake prescribed medications. In the EU, various drug 
   suppliers ensure drug authenticity using a ‘point-of-dispense’ verification system. NAPRA is an association that 
   governs pharmacies across Canada.

   Pharmacies in various regions encourage effective policies to evaluate refill demand. Therefore, The pharmacy management 
   system adopts security measures to stay updated with the latest compliance needs.
</p>



